581005

Diapensiaceae

NORTH CAROLINA FLORA

Species *Galax urceolata* (Poirot) Brummitt

Date 4 February 2002        County Cumberland

Location Rockfish Creek, about half a mile downstream
from Lake Upchurch, at U-shape bend.

Habitat Steep north-facing slope about 20 feet high,
much of it open and with some seepage. Common up
near crest under *Kalmia latifolia*, *Clethra alnifolia*,
*Vaccinium elliottii*, *Chamaecyparis thyoides*, *Cyrilla
racemiflora*. With *Hexastylis minor*.

B.A. Sorrie 10839
